{
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "intro",
      "title": "",
      "text": "This project investigates how text-to-image generation models represent people and social roles. Systems such as Stable Diffusion can produce synthetic images from textual descriptions, but what appears to be neutral image generation is actually shaped by technical choices, datasets, and infrastructures that influence what the model is able to represent.",
      "images": []
    },
    {
      "id": "laion-intro",
      "type": "laion",
      "text": "The images produced by these systems do not emerge from nothing. Models learn correlations between words and images from the datasets on which they are trained. The composition of these datasets—what they include and what they exclude—determines which visual associations the model learns and which representations it tends to reproduce.",
      "laionDensity": 0,
      "showCaptions": false
    },
    {
      "id": "laion-1",
      "type": "laion",
      "text": "Stable Diffusion was trained on LAION, one of the largest image datasets available. This archive contains billions of image–text pairs collected from the web and forms the basis through which the model learns to connect textual descriptions with visual content.",
      "laionDensity": 0.20,
      "showCaptions": false
    },
    {
      "id": "laion-2",
      "type": "laion",
      "text": "Within the LAION dataset, images are associated with short textual descriptions, often derived from the alt text found on web pages. The model learns by observing these pairs: on one side the image, on the other the text describing it. Through this process it builds statistical relationships between words and visual features.",
      "laionDensity": 0.40,
      "showCaptions": true
    },
    {
      "id": "laion-3",
      "type": "laion",
      "text": "LAION is built through automated web scraping. Images are not selected through human review but filtered through algorithms that measure the similarity between image and text. This process enables the collection of enormous quantities of data, but it also reduces control over the content included.",
      "laionDensity": 1.0,
      "showCaptions": true
    },
    {
      "id": "laion-zoomout",
      "type": "laion-zoomout",
      "text": "LAION operates at an extreme scale: billions of images sourced from websites, commercial platforms, and online archives. This scale strengthens the dataset statistically, but it also makes manual inspection or verification practically impossible.",
      "laionDensity": 1.0,
      "showCaptions": false,
      "zoomLevel": 3
    },
